<title>WHY WE NEED THE DEFENSE OF MARRIAGE ACT</title>

<body>

<center><img src="/townhall/FRC/podium/podium.gif">

<h2>WHY WE NEED THE<br>
DEFENSE OF MARRIAGE ACT</h2>

<p><hr size=3 width=50%><p>

<i>by<br>
Robert H. Knight</i></center>

<p>

<i>This speech was presented at a July 2, 1996 Capitol Hill briefing
regarding the Defense of Marriage Act (DOMA).  The briefing was
sponsored by the Family Research Council.</i>

<p>

The thing I hear most often in debates about the Defense of Marriage
Act is, &quot;Who will it hurt if two gays or two lesbians down
the street want to share their love?&quot;

<p>

Well, if you put it that way, the answer is almost nobody, if
they keep it entirely to themselves and their behavior does not
involve the transmission of AIDS and other diseases that are epidemic
among homosexuals. That is probably unrealistic.  And they hurt
themselves in living a less fulfilling life.

<p>

Most Americans believe in the philosophy of  &quot;live and let
live.&quot; They don't want to make the plight of homosexuals
any more difficult than it already is.  But tolerance is not what
homosexual activists are seeking.  They are demanding that society
elevate homosexuality to the moral level of marriage.   When they
bring the law into it, they are no longer just minding their own
business but imposing it on every single citizen.

<p>

If you are a devout Christian, Jew or Muslim, or merely someone
who believes homosexuality is immoral and harmful, and the law
declares homosexuality a protected status, then your personal
beliefs are now outside civil law.  This has very serious implications,
for if the law declares opposition to homosexuality as bigotry,
then the entire power of the civil rights apparatus can be brought
against you.

<p>

Businessmen will have to subsidize homosexuality or face legal
sanctions.  Schoolchildren will have to be taught that homosexuality
is the equivalent of marital love.  Religious people will be told
their beliefs are no longer valid, and their independence will
be challenged.

<p>

While homosexuals say they want only tolerance, they are being
dishonest.  They already have tolerance, but are aiming for government-
and corporate-mandated acceptance.  Where gay rights have become
law, people of conscience are already being targeted for punishment
in the name of &quot;diversity&quot; training.

<p>

The Boy Scouts of America are under legal attack in the states
which have special rights for &quot;sexual orientation.&quot;
The Scouts, a private group, are being told to abandon their
moral code of more than 80 years and to place young boys under
homosexual men on camping trips -- or face financial ruin.  The
attack against the Scouts is really an attack on parents, because
parents have the right, in a free nation, to entrust their children
to organizations that reflect the parents' most deeply held beliefs.
If they cannot do this, then we are living in tyranny.  That
is the real, ugly side of gay rights that the media will not show
-- the tyrannical reality.

<p>

Here's an example of where we are headed.  In Hamilton, Ontario,
the mayor was asked by homosexual activists to declare a &quot;gay
pride week.&quot;  Hamilton being a blue-collar, largely Catholic
town, the mayor declined.  He was hauled before a human rights
commission, personally fined $5,000, and told that he had committed
the crimes of &quot;gay bashing&quot; and hatemongering.

<p>

If homosexuals achieve the power to force others to pretend that
their unions are &quot;marriages,&quot; then people of conscience
will be told to ignore their God-given beliefs and to support
what they regard as immoral and destructive.

<p>

Homosexuality has been discouraged in all cultures because it
is inherently wrong and harmful to individuals, families and societies.
The only reason it has been able to gain such prominence in America
today is the near blackout on information about homosexual behavior
itself.  We are being treated to a steady drumbeat of propaganda
echoing the stolen rhetoric of the black civil rights movement
and misrepresenting science.

<p>

Here are some of the myths:

<p>

<b>The 10 percent estimate of homosexuality in the population.</b>
Based entirely on the discredited Kinsey studies, the figure
is a fiction.  The reality is nearer to 1 percent or, at most,
2 percent.

<p>

<b>Genetic studies.</b> Activists say homosexuality is just
like skin color.  But there are thousands of former homosexuals,
but no former blacks or Hispanics.  Virtually all gay genetic
studies have been done by homosexual activists.  All have huge
methodological flaws, and many point to the opposite conclusion
-- that homosexuality is a learned behavior rather than in-born.

<p>

<b>Gay teen suicide.</b> We are told that one in three teen suicides
are gay teens, but this comes from a single report that was repudiated
by Health and Human Services Secretary Louis Sullivan.  Other
studies repudiate the figure as well.

<p>

<b>Psychological studies.</b> In the 1950s, UCLA psychologist
Evelyn Hooker conducted three tests comparing groups of 30 hand-picked
homosexual men with 30 randomly-selected heterosexual men.  In
two of the three tests, the gays were easily picked out because
they sexualized their drawings.  Yet this study was cited in 1973
as the centerpiece of research leading the American Psychiatric
Association and the American Psychological Association to remove
homosexuality from their lists of emotional disorders.

<p>

<b>Hospital visitation.</b> Homosexuals claim that they have
difficulty visiting loved ones in hospitals because families have
primary visitation rights.  Yet an informal survey of hospitals
in the Washington, D.C. area and other metro areas reveals that
no homosexuals are being denied any visitation rights.  A Nexis
search of July 2, 1996 also shows no news stories about homosexuals
being denied visitation rights.  It's a non-issue manufactured
to foster the &quot;victim&quot; image that homosexuals use to
advance their agenda.

<p>

<b>Military security studies.</b> During the debate over gays
in the military, the government unveiled a study that included
a chapter on the moral history of America.  It was full of anti-religious
sentiment and was written by a man who sits on the board of a
journal that promotes man-boy sex.

<p>

<b>Gay parenting studies.</b> Conducted and evaluated by lesbians
or homosexuals, these studies have major problems, but even so,
indicate that children in homosexual households are four times
more likely to identify as homosexual or get involved in homosexual
behavior than children raised in single-parent households.

<p>

I could go on.  Suffice to say, America is being fed a diet of
propaganda that has gone largely unexamined by major media.  The
point is to create the falsehood that homosexuality is normal,
healthy and of no consequence, and should be accorded the same
treatment in the law as benign characteristics such as skin color
or ethnicity.

<p>

The language of gay rights is tolerance, but the aim is raw power
to criminalize dissent from the view that &quot;gay is good.&quot;
In the name of freedom, this agenda must be exposed and halted.
A good place to start would be the passage of the Defense of
Marriage Act.

<p>

<center>***</center>

<p>

<i>Robert H. Knight is the director of cultural studies at the
Family Research Council, a Washington, D.C.-based research and
education organziation.  Knight is a former news editor and writer
for </i>The Los Angeles Times<i>, a 1989-1990 Media Fellow at
the Hoover Institution at Stanford University, and a former Senior
Fellow for Cultural Policy Studies at the Heritage Foundation.</i>

<p>

<center>
