<html>

<title>THE DEFENSE OF MARRIAGE ACT: AN INSIDER'S VIEW</title>

<body>

<center><img src="/townhall/FRC/podium/podium.gif">

<h2>THE<br>
DEFENSE OF MARRIAGE ACT:<br>
AN INSIDER'S VIEW</h2>

<p><hr size=3 width=50%><p>

<i>by<br>
Anthony Falzarano</i></center>

<p>

<i>This speech was given at a July 2, 1996 Capitol Hill briefing
regarding the Defense Of Marriage Act (DOMA).  The briefing was
sponsored by the Family Research Council.</i>

<p>

My name is Anthony Falzarano.  I am the executive director of
Transformation Ex-Gay Christian Ministries of Washington, D.C.
We are the Washington, D.C.-affiliate of the largest ex-gay network
in the world, Exodus International, which is based in San Rafael,
California.

<p>

I am here this morning standing in solidarity with the rest of
my colleagues to voice my strong approval of The Defense of Marriage
Act (more commonly known as DOMA).  I really find it incredible
that this bill would even have to come before the halls of Congress.
For many years the term &quot;marriage&quot; never had to be
defined because this country was founded on Judeo-Christian beliefs.
Our founding fathers looked to our heavenly Creator for His definition
of marriage in the pages of the Holy Scriptures in the following:
Genesis 2:24, Matthew 19:5, Mark 10:7, and Ephesians 5:31.  It's
a sad day for America when we would even have to debate this issue
publicly.  The United States of America has taken a dangerous
moral nosedive in the last 35 years and it's about time that we
say &quot;enough is enough&quot; to the enemies of this country
that we have allowed to infiltrate the halls of Congress with
their voices of destruction.

<p>

The politically-motivated homosexual movement in this country
has stepped over the line.  This movement is extremely well funded
and well connected.  It has been working for the last 30 years
like an army of termites, secretly eating away the floorboards
of moral integrity in this country.  It is time to expose the
agenda of these gay political organizations and call them what
they are -- evil.  The gay community shocked us in the 1970s by
coming out of the closet, gained our sympathy in the 1980s with
the horrible pandemic called AIDS and is now trying to force our
acceptance of their lifestyle using the legal system of this country.

<p>

I speak to you today not just as an observer of this movement,
but as one of them.  I am a former homosexual.  I lived that lifestyle
from the time I was 17 until I was 26.  I entered the gay lifestyle
thinking that there really wasn't any choice for me.  What I didn't
realize is that, although I didn't choose to be homosexual, I
did not have to be gay.  I had a choice.  I could change my orientation
from gay to straight.  My healing process was a long and difficult
one.  However, change is possible.  The four national ex-gay networks
are currently ministering to more than 10,000 former homosexuals.
Many of us are sick and tired of a lifestyle that initially seems
very freeing but eventually puts us in all kinds of bondage and
eventually will kill us.  I have lost over 35 of my friends and
acquaintances to the disease of AIDS and don't want to see one
more person become infected with this deadly disease.  The organized
gay community is telling us that AIDS is no longer a gay disease
and although it is spreading into the heterosexual population
in this country very quickly, 61 percent of people that are coming
down with this deadly disease in the U.S. are homosexual, according
to the Centers for Disease Control in Atlanta.

<p>

The gay lobbyists in this country do not want DOMA to pass.  They
know that they cannot force the homosexual agenda into the organized
Christian churches in America (although they are trying), so they
are attempting to push their agenda on the American public and
the civil government using the argument that &quot;they are being
discriminated against.&quot;  I say that their cries of discrimination
have been grossly exaggerated.  When I was a homosexual, as long
as I didn't push my lifestyle into the face of my landlord, no
one kept me from getting an apartment.  As long as I didn't push
my sexual preference into the face of my employer, no one ever
denied me a job.

<p>

America must take a very strong stand against the very highly
organized gay community in this country by supporting The Defense
of Marriage Act.  If we don't say &quot;no&quot; to the organized
gay community now, the United States will suffer the consequences
of our complacency.  America needs to start helping homosexuals
recover from their sexual brokenness.  Putting a stamp of approval
on a lifestyle by legally recognizing it (and even calling it
marriage) is not really helping homosexuals.  It's perpetuating
a myth and delivering them over to a deathstyle.  Just take a
look back into the history books, when homosexuality was openly
accepted into the civil governments of the Greeks and Romans.
Shortly thereafter God passed judgment on those civilizations
and they ceased to exist.  Please don't allow history to repeat
itself.  America isn't bleeding spiritually, it's hemorrhaging.
Please don't allow history to repeat itself.

<p>

<center>***</center>

<p>

<i>Anthony Falzarano is executive director of Transformation Ministries.
Falzarano is a former homosexual who has ministered to more than
500 former homosexuals and has served as a media spokesman on</i> 
CBS, ABC, The BBC, USA Radio Network <i>and many other
media outlets.  He has testified before the Montgomery County,
Maryland Board of Education, Maryland General Assembly and the
Fairfax County Board of Supervisors regarding homosexual issues.</i>

<p>

<center>
<b>
[<a href="/townhall/FRC/podium/">Other At The Podiums</a>] 
[<a href="/townhall/FRC/policypapers.html">Other Policy Papers</a>]
[<a href="/townhall/FRC/reproduce/reproduc.html">Reproducing This 
Article</a>]
</b>

