<TITLE>JACK KEMP -- Heritage </TITLE>


<H3>JACK KEMP</H3>
<B>DISTINGUISHED FELLOW</B>
<P><IMG SRC="/heritage/staff/pics/kemp.jpe" ALIGN=LEFT HSPACE=10>
<P>
Kemp, a long-time champion of supply-side economics and "empowerment" strategies to help the poor, served as Housing and Urban Development Secretary during the Bush administration. A former nine-term congressman representing Buffalo, N.Y., Kemp was a 1988 candidate for the Republican presidential nomination.

<p>
Mr. Kemp resigned from The Heritage Foundation on August 14, 1996, to pursue the office of Vice-President of the United States.<p>
 
<BR><HR WIDTH="30%"><BR><CENTER><A HREF="/heritage/hbut.map"><IMG SRC="/heritage/hbut.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A></CENTER></BODY>
